Have you heard?

102
00:18:36,978 --> 00:18:38,646
I have heard loud and clear, 
 you damned worthless bastards.

103
00:18:38,646 --> 00:18:42,383
To silence us, you have done the un-imaginable...

104
00:19:03,871 --> 00:19:08,809
I am hungry, give me money.

105
00:19:08,809 --> 00:19:12,245
Ah....Stinks!!!

106
00:19:12,245 --> 00:19:15,816
I don't have any money, go away!

107
00:19:22,758 --> 00:19:28,392
Are you okay, Bong Soon?

108
00:19:28,392 --> 00:19:32,199
Hey, you think you can do anything if you are a son of noble family?

109
00:19:32,199 --> 00:19:33,934
I'm sorry.

110
00:19:33,934 --> 00:19:35,704
I didn't mean to ...

111
00:19:35,704 --> 00:19:44,245
You little bastards! Go away!!! How dare you act like this to my young master!!! Bastards!!!

112
00:19:44,245 --> 00:19:47,315
Young master, are you okay?

113
00:19:47,315 --> 00:19:49,382
Yes.

114
00:19:51,886 --> 00:19:53,488
Let's go Gyeom.

115
00:19:53,488 --> 00:19:56,856
Yes, father.

116
00:19:56,856 --> 00:20:01,595
Wow! What a meticulous work as if you measured with ruler..!!!

117
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:06,862
Ah, Prosecutor General's wife is asking for you to drop by.

118
00:20:06,862 --> 00:20:11,873
It seems that she is very happy with your sewing skills from last time....

119
00:20:11,873 --> 00:20:14,575
Really?

120
00:20:17,378 --> 00:20:21,015
Cha Dol, stay here and play for a while.

121
00:20:21,015 --> 00:20:23,384
I have to visit the ProsecutorÂ´s Office.

122
00:20:23,384 --> 00:20:25,219
Yes, mother.

123
00:20:43,205 --> 00:20:45,639
Who is that rascal?

124
00:20:45,639 --> 00:20:47,942
Insolent!

125
00:20:47,942 --> 00:20:49,811
Him?

126
00:20:49,811 --> 00:20:51,178
You know him?

127
00:20:51,178 --> 00:20:54,682
His father is a notorious petty thief 
 who has been in and out of jail.

128
00:20:54,682 --> 00:20:57,919
They say that his mother's a runaway slave...

129
00:20:57,919 --> 00:21:01,089
I see that he gets his lowly bloodline from both sides.

130
00:21:01,089 --> 00:21:06,193
So that low class kid bumped into me 
 and dared to just run off like that?

131
00:21:06,193 --> 00:21:11,198
He doesn't know his place and is very arrogant. 
 Many people would like to teach him a lesson.

132
00:21:11,198 --> 00:21:16,904
Then we should remind him 
 what dirty blood runs through his veins.

133
00:22:40,344 --> 00:22:53,239
Thief, thief! There's a thief! There's a thief over there! There is a thief!

134
00:22:53,239 --> 00:22:55,355
Young master, what's the matter?

135
00:22:55,355 --> 00:22:58,464
A thief has stolen that man's belongings.

136
00:23:04,942 --> 00:23:11,386
My lord, are you missing anything, sir?

137
00:23:11,386 --> 00:23:13,484
Oh, actually, yes.

138
00:23:13,484 --> 00:23:16,567
Has young master by any chance seen the face of the thief?

139
00:23:16,567 --> 00:23:19,698
I saw it.

140
00:23:19,698 --> 00:23:24,717
Young master saw his face? Who is it?

141
00:23:32,893 --> 00:23:36,733
I am not a thief. I really don't know what's going on.

142
00:23:42,532 --> 00:23:44,518
Oh my god....That was fast....!

143
00:23:44,518 --> 00:23:48,802
I......no.....

144
00:23:48,802 --> 00:23:53,922
What in the world...

145
00:23:53,922 --> 00:23:55,150
Well....My lord...

146
00:24:01,413 --> 00:24:05,050
I heard that his father is a thief, too.

147
00:24:05,050 --> 00:24:08,680
You can't expect anything better from such lowly blood.

148
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:12,420
No, no! My dad is not a thief!

149
00:24:13,697 --> 00:24:17,426
Hey you guys are working hard here.

150
00:24:21,437 --> 00:24:28,665
Whoa! Isn't this Woohwang Chungshimhwan 
 made in Ming (heart calming medicine) that I always hear about?

151
00:24:28,665 --> 00:24:29,858
What's the matter?

152
00:24:29,858 --> 00:24:38,609
There's a tip off that the fake Woohwang Chungshimhwan are being smuggled into our country.

153
00:24:38,609 --> 00:24:41,726
We don't do such things. 
 Go ahead and search all you want.

154
00:24:41,726 --> 00:24:48,244
Really? I heard that all smuggling items are hidden in the bottom of the boat.

155
00:24:48,244 --> 00:24:49,910
Then lift it up...

156
00:24:49,910 --> 00:24:51,752
Lift it up?

157
00:24:51,752 --> 00:24:55,395
Open those boxes for me, quickly!

158
00:24:55,395 --> 00:24:57,321
Come on....What the...

